  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nIf the duration text starts with a digit, SchedulerUtils adds \"PT\" prefix.\r\nhttps://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/main/extensions/scheduler/common/src/main/java/io/quarkus/scheduler/common/runtime/util/SchedulerUtils.java#L178\r\n\r\nThis works for hours, minutes and seconds, but not for days, as it causes `DateTimeParseException` with the message \"Text cannot be parsed to a Duration\".\r\nSee \"Examples\" at https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/Duration.html#parse-java.lang.CharSequence- .\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI can either define Scheduler annotation `every` property as `1D` or the documentation states the limitation about having to use `P1D`.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe app won't start throwing `IllegalStateExcption` caused by `DateTimeParseException` with the message \"Text cannot be parsed to a Duration\".\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n_No response_\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
